## API Call - URL Description
|API Call|Method|URL Endpoint|Description|
|-----------|--------|-------|-------------|
|login|POST|/api/login|To authenticate the Anonymous user|
|getContext|GET|/api/{apiVer}/CtxDto|To get the panchayat data ex: State, District, Division, Mandal, Panchayat etc..|
|getStagingHostname"/"getHostname|GET|/api/1/Route/qats |To get the hostname/ staging hostname|
|logout|GET|/api/logout|To logout the Anonymous user|

### Description : 
To get the host name from Gs-Route server  
1. Invoke the api call invokeRouteAuth (https://{hostname}/api/login)  
    - If the response is 200 then save the response data response data ( Authorization, s-jwt-token, set-cookie) in preference helper preference and invoke the api call getContext ( https://{hostname}/api/{apiVer}/CtxDto ).  
    - If the response is other than 200 then show error message  
2. If the response from api call getContext is 200 then invoke the api all getStagingHostname (or) getHostname ( https://{hostname}/api/{apiVer}/Route/qats ).  
    - If the response is other than 200 then show error message  
3. If the response from api call getStagingHostname (or) getHostname is 200 then get the response routeChiperData, prepare the RouteData object, save it in database and invoke api call routingLogout ( https://{hostname}/api/logout ).  
    - If the response is other than 200 then show error message  
4. If the response from api call routingLogout is other than 200 then show error message

### Flow of Routing API Calls
{{<mermaid align="center">}}
graph TD 
	start((Start))
	loginApiCall{API Call : login}
	getContextApiCall{API Call : getContext}
	getHostNameApiCall{API Call : getStagingHostname / getHostName}
	routingLogoutApiCall{API Call : routingLogout}
	error1>error]
	error2>error]
	error3>error]
	error4>error]
	end1((end))
	start-->loginApiCall
	loginApiCall--Response!=200-->error1
	loginApiCall--Response==200-->getContextApiCall
	getContextApiCall--Response!=200-->error2
    getContextApiCall--Response==200-->getHostNameApiCall
	getHostNameApiCall--Response!=200-->error3
    getHostNameApiCall--Response==200-->routingLogoutApiCall
    routingLogoutApiCall--Response!=200-->error4
    routingLogoutApiCall--Response==200-->end1

	
{{< /mermaid >}}

### Routing Module & GS-Route Operations :

{{<mermaid align="center">}}
sequenceDiagram
	participant SQLite as SQLite Database
    participant Login as Login Module
    participant Net as Network Utils
    participant Route as GS-Route
    autonumber

    rect rgb(244,244,244)
        Login->>+SQLite: get RouteHostname
        SQLite-->>-Login: RouteData Object

        Login->>+Net: Check Internet , invokeRouteAuth
        Net--x-Login: F : Connection Error
        Login->>+Route: S : POST https://{hostname}/api/login invokeRouteAuth
        Route-->>-Login: RES 200
        
        Login->>+Net: Check Internet , getContext
        Net--x-Login: F : Connection Error
        Login->>+Route: S : POST https://{hostname}/api/{apiVer}/CtxDto getContext
        Route-->>-Login: RES 200

        Login->>+Net: Check Internet , invokeToGetDomain
        Net--x-Login: F: Connection Error
        Login->>+Route: S : GET https://{hostname}/api/{apiVer}/Route/qats getStagingHostname/getHostname
        Route-->>-Login: RES 200

        Note right of Login: If RouteData == null { insert RouteData } else { update Route Data }
        Login->>+SQLite: persistInLocalDB(RouteData routeData)

        Login->>+Net: Check Internet , routingLogout
        Net--x-Login: F : Connection Error
        Login->>+Route: S : GET https://{hostname}/api/logout routingLogout
        Route-->>-Login: RES 200
    end
